        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-11-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-11-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="269" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Pike</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 33.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-11-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 23, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of November 6 (No. 25) has just
                    been received. I have already anticipated and disposed of the principal subject
                    which it presents.</p>
                <p>Felicitate the government of the Netherlands as we felicitate ourselves on the
                    renewed auguries of good and cordial relations between friends too old to be
                    alienated thoughtlessly, or from mere impatience.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James S. Pike</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
